The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Lloyd raps Pathan
 - Youngster found guilty of violating rules of fairplay  Irfan Pathan claps after dismissing Damien Martyn in Sydney on Sunday Sydney: Irfan Pathan has been reprimanded for breaching crickets Code of Conduct as Indias long tour of Australia ended on a sour note on Monday. Pathan was found guilty of violating the rules of fairplay after making a mocking gesture towards Damien Martyn following his dismissal in Sundays second tri-series final. Pathan, 19, was reported under the ICCs strict rules on player behaviour by the two field umpires Rudi Koertzen and Daryl Harper as well as the third umpire Simon Taufel. He was ordered to attend a hearing at the end of play and Match Referee Clive Lloyd issued a statement on Monday saying the paceman had been reprimanded for a Level 1 breach. Its important that players and team officials at all times conduct themselves, Lloyd said. Meanwhile, India (105 points) remained in sixth place in the ICC ODI championship table. The world champions consolidated their position atop the standings with 137. (Reuters)  Copyright 
